To recover these files you can use the FIX (or DECRYPT) or the STABILIZE command, which attempts to synchronize the file using a frequency value.
<HR>
Example: [FIX FILENAME 8000] OR [STABILIZE FILENAME]
<HR>
STABILIZE command opens a stabilization interface where you can adjust the frequency manually using the arrow keys.
Arrow keys change the frequency, Shift + arrows make finer adjustments, and Enter confirms the tuning.
<HR>
The goal is to match the file’s hidden ideal frequency so it becomes readable.